.TH start-cli-backup-history 1  "history "
.SH NAME
start\-cli\-backup\-history \- Commands to inspect automatic backup checkpoint history
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBstart\-cli backup history\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Commands to inspect automatic backup checkpoint history
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-history\-delete\-archived(1)
Delete selected archived automatic backup checkpoints
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-history\-discover(1)
Discover automatic backup history stored on a backup target
.TP
start\-cli\-backup\-history\-list(1)
List automatic backup checkpoint history
